commit 52289195b5eb7171e61b0cc31a62a5e3aa0e6110
Author: Mike Wright <mike@softwarewrighter.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 15 12:59:55 2026 -0700

    feat(compiler): raise INPUT_BUF_SIZE to 131072 and report truncation (closes #19)

    Fourth bump (8192 -> 16384 -> 32768 -> 65536 -> 131072). The previous
    65536-byte buffer hit exactly 0x10000, silently truncating sw-cor24-ocaml
    at ~1483 lines and producing cascading "expected X (got EOF)" errors.

    Also add explicit truncation diagnostic: if the source exceeds the
    buffer before EOT, drain the rest and emit a clear error instead of
    a misleading parse-error cascade:

      ; ERROR: source exceeds compiler input buffer (131072 bytes)

    This makes future ceiling hits obvious instead of cryptic.

    Closes #19
    Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

