{ Run GC every 8th REPL iteration. Each transaction allocates AST
  and intermediate values; collecting once per transaction is
  O(N²) overhead via the iterative fixed-point. Batching across
  iterations lets garbage from N transactions be reclaimed in one
  sweep, amortizing the cost. heap_limit overflow would force-trip
  collection earlier (TODO: add overflow trampoline). }
gc_skip := gc_skip + 1;
if gc_skip >= 8 then begin gc_collect; gc_skip := 0 end;

